101. Rev Esp Patol. 2018 Apr - Jun;51(2):134-137. doi: 10.1016/j.patol.2017.05.003.Epub 2017 Jul 3.[Primary breast synovial sarcoma].[Article in Spanish]Alfaro-Cervelló C(1), Burgués O(2).Author information: (1)Servicio de Anatomía Patológica, Hospital Clínico Universitario de Valencia,Valencia, España. Electronic address: clara.alfaro@uv.es.(2)Servicio de Anatomía Patológica, Hospital Clínico Universitario de Valencia,Valencia, España.Primary synovial sarcoma of the breast is very rare. We report a case of a33-year-old woman, who had previously undergone a radical mastectomy, having beendiagnosed with fusocellular breast carcinoma. Histopathology revealed ahypercellular lesion formed by spindle cells with storiform and herringbonepatterns. Immunohistochemistry showed strong expression of vimentin and CD99, andfocal bcl2, EMA, CK AE1-AE3, actin and desmin, with negativity for S100, CD34,CK7, CK14, CK19, hormone receptors, caldesmon and myosin. Molecular biologyrevealed the expression of the fusion product of the SS18 and SSX genes,indicative of the translocation t(X;18)(p11.2;q11.2), which confirmed thediagnosis of synovial sarcoma.Copyright © 2017 Sociedad Española de Anatomía Patológica. Publicado por ElsevierEspaña, S.L.U. All rights reserved.DOI: 10.1016/j.patol.2017.05.003 PMID: 29602375 